From: Tobias Klauser <tklauser@distanz.ch>
Date: Tue, 20 May 2014 08:23:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 070/144] i40evf: Use is_multicast_ether_addr helper
Patch-mainline: v3.16-rc1
Git-commit: dc5f2de6f8f64f97f3cb7edfe6aed34801e358d8
References: bsc#909486 FATE#317393

Use the is_multicast_ether_addr helper function from linux/etherdevice.h
instead of open coding the multicast address check.

Signed-off-by: Tobias Klauser <tklauser@distanz.ch>
Tested-by: Sibai Li <sibai.li@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40evf/i40evf_main.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40evf/i40evf_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40evf/i40evf_main.c
@@ -842,7 +842,7 @@ static void i40evf_set_rx_mode(struct ne
 	list_for_each_entry_safe(f, ftmp, &adapter->mac_filter_list, list) {
 		bool found = false;
 
-		if (f->macaddr[0] & 0x01) {
+		if (is_multicast_ether_addr(f->macaddr)) {
 			netdev_for_each_mc_addr(mca, netdev) {
 				if (ether_addr_equal(mca->addr, f->macaddr)) {
 					found = true;
